<span typeof="mw:File"><span><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/Dialog-warning.svg/40px-Dialog-warning.svg.png" decoding="async" width="25" height="25" class="mw-file-element" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/Dialog-warning.svg/50px-Dialog-warning.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="48" data-file-height="48"></span></span> <small>You must also include a <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Copyright_tags/Country-specific_tags#United_States_of_America" title="Commons:Copyright tags/Country-specific tags">United States public domain tag</a> to indicate why this work is in the public domain in the United States.<div class="navigation-not-searchable"> Note that a few countries have copyright terms longer than 70 years: Mexico has 100 years, Jamaica has 95 years, Colombia has 80 years, and Guatemala and Samoa have 75 years. This image may <i>not</i> be in the public domain in these countries, which moreover do <i>not</i> implement the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/rule_of_the_shorter_term" class="extiw" title="w:rule of the shorter term">rule of the shorter term</a>. Honduras has a general copyright term of 75 years, but it <i>does</i> implement the rule of the shorter term. Copyright may extend on works created by French who died for France in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_War_II" class="extiw" title="w:World War II">World War II</a> (<a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Copyright_rules_by_territory/France" title="Commons:Copyright rules by territory/France">more information</a>), Russians who served in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eastern_Front_(World_War_II)" class="extiw" title="w:Eastern Front (World War II)">the Eastern Front of World War II</a> (known as the Great Patriotic War in Russia) and posthumously <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rehabilitation_(Soviet)" class="extiw" title="w:Rehabilitation (Soviet)">rehabilitated</a> victims of Soviet repressions (<a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:PD-Russia" title="Template:PD-Russia">more information</a>).</div></small>

<p>This work is in the <b><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/public_domain" class="extiw" title="en:public domain">public domain</a></b> in its country of origin and other countries and areas where the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_countries%27_copyright_lengths" class="extiw" title="w:List of countries' copyright lengths">copyright term</a> is the author's <b>life plus 70 years or fewer</b>.
</p>
<hr>
<span typeof="mw:File"><span><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/Dialog-warning.svg/40px-Dialog-warning.svg.png" decoding="async" width="25" height="25" class="mw-file-element" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/Dialog-warning.svg/50px-Dialog-warning.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="48" data-file-height="48"></span></span> <small>You must also include a <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Copyright_tags/Country-specific_tags#United_States_of_America" title="Commons:Copyright tags/Country-specific tags">United States public domain tag</a> to indicate why this work is in the public domain in the United States.<div class="navigation-not-searchable"> Note that a few countries have copyright terms longer than 70 years: Mexico has 100 years, Jamaica has 95 years, Colombia has 80 years, and Guatemala and Samoa have 75 years. This image may <i>not</i> be in the public domain in these countries, which moreover do <i>not</i> implement the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/rule_of_the_shorter_term" class="extiw" title="w:rule of the shorter term">rule of the shorter term</a>. Honduras has a general copyright term of 75 years, but it <i>does</i> implement the rule of the shorter term. Copyright may extend on works created by French who died for France in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_War_II" class="extiw" title="w:World War II">World War II</a> (<a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Copyright_rules_by_territory/France" title="Commons:Copyright rules by territory/France">more information</a>), Russians who served in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eastern_Front_(World_War_II)" class="extiw" title="w:Eastern Front (World War II)">the Eastern Front of World War II</a> (known as the Great Patriotic War in Russia) and posthumously <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rehabilitation_(Soviet)" class="extiw" title="w:Rehabilitation (Soviet)">rehabilitated</a> victims of Soviet repressions (<a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:PD-Russia" title="Template:PD-Russia">more information</a>).</div></small>

class="mbox-text" style="text-align:center; padding:10px;">This <b><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/insignia" class="extiw" title="en:insignia">insignia</a></b> has not been confirmed to be source.</span><br><small><b>HELP</b>: (<b>1</b>) The picture claims to be authentic. As such, “<b>own work</b>” is no proper source by itself. If applicable, any provided source(s) doesn't show an <b>original depiction</b> nor an <b>original description</b>, and therefore may violate <b><a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Project_scope/Neutral_point_of_view" title="Commons:Project scope/Neutral point of view">NPOV</a></b> (<i>neutral point of view</i>) by being <b><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:No_original_research" class="extiw" title="w:Wikipedia:No original research">original research</a></b>. (<b>2</b>) For coat of arms please use the <b><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/blazon" class="extiw" title="en:blazon">blazon</a></b> and/or the picture of an original interpretation to provide an adequate source, but at least one or more references to literature. (<b>3</b>) If this depiction is a derivative please use the <b><a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:Derived_from" title="Template:Derived from">Template: Derived from</a></b> to avoid sequence errors, to make this work more transparent for others to view and investigate, and to avoid an <b>infringement of the copyright licence</b>.</small></td></tr></tbody></table>
Permission: Please note that this applies only to the coat of arms <b>definition</b> (composition / description). The <b>representation</b> of a coat of arms is an artistic creation, subject as such to copyright laws.
<p><b>Restriction of use - Legal notice:</b><br>Most of the time, the usage of coats of arms is <b>governed by legal restrictions</b>, independent of the  status of the depiction shown here. A coat of arms represents its owner. Though it can be freely represented, it cannot be appropriated, or used in such a way as to create a confusion with or a prejudice to its owner. 
</p>
<b>Usage on Commons</b>:<br>Please provide licence information for the coat of arm representation, information for the author of the picture, and the source if not self-made work.

<td><i>This image is in the <b><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/public_domain" class="extiw" title="w:public domain">public domain</a></b> in Norway because images not considered to be "works of art" become public domain 50 years after creation, provided that more than 15 years have passed since the photographer's death or the photographer is unknown.</i>
<p>This is according to <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://lovdata.no/lov/2018-06-15-40/%C2%A723">§ 23</a> in the Norwegian <a href="https://no.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%85ndsverkloven" class="extiw" title="no:Åndsverkloven">Åndsverkloven</a>.
</p><p>Under the former photo law, protection ended 25 years after creation, provided that more than 15 years had passed since the photographer's death or the photographer is unknown. The image is in the public domain if the protection ended before 29 June 1995 under the older term.<a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://lovdata.no/dokument/NL/lov/1995-06-23-37">[1]</a>
</p>
<hr>
<div style="text-align:center; font-size:smaller;">To uploader: <b>Please provide information about where the image was first published, who created it, and when the photographer died, if known. The right to be attributed does not expire in Norway.</b></div>
<hr>
<p><small>Images uploaded to Wikimedia Commons must also be in the public domain in the United States. A Norwegian work that is in the public domain in Norway is in the public domain in the U.S. only if it was in the public domain in Norway in 1996 and no copyright was registered in the U.S. (This is the effect of <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.copyright.gov/title17/92chap1.html#104a">17 USC 104A</a> with its critical date of January 1, 1996.)</small>
</p>

<p>This work is in the <b><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/public_domain" class="extiw" title="en:public domain">public domain</a></b> in its country of origin and other countries and areas where the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_countries%27_copyright_lengths" class="extiw" title="w:List of countries' copyright lengths">copyright term</a> is the author's <b>life plus 70 years or fewer</b>.
</p>

<span typeof="mw:File"><span><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/Dialog-warning.svg/40px-Dialog-warning.svg.png" decoding="async" width="25" height="25" class="mw-file-element" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/Dialog-warning.svg/50px-Dialog-warning.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="48" data-file-height="48"></span></span> <small>You must also include a <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Copyright_tags/Country-specific_tags#United_States_of_America" title="Commons:Copyright tags/Country-specific tags">United States public domain tag</a> to indicate why this work is in the public domain in the United States.<div class="navigation-not-searchable"> Note that a few countries have copyright terms longer than 70 years: Mexico has 100 years, Jamaica has 95 years, Colombia has 80 years, and Guatemala and Samoa have 75 years. This image may <i>not</i> be in the public domain in these countries, which moreover do <i>not</i> implement the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/rule_of_the_shorter_term" class="extiw" title="w:rule of the shorter term">rule of the shorter term</a>. Honduras has a general copyright term of 75 years, but it <i>does</i> implement the rule of the shorter term. Copyright may extend on works created by French who died for France in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_War_II" class="extiw" title="w:World War II">World War II</a> (<a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Copyright_rules_by_territory/France" title="Commons:Copyright rules by territory/France">more information</a>), Russians who served in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eastern_Front_(World_War_II)" class="extiw" title="w:Eastern Front (World War II)">the Eastern Front of World War II</a> (known as the Great Patriotic War in Russia) and posthumously <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rehabilitation_(Soviet)" class="extiw" title="w:Rehabilitation (Soviet)">rehabilitated</a> victims of Soviet repressions (<a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:PD-Russia" title="Template:PD-Russia">more information</a>).</div></small>
</td></tr>

Title: File:The Creation of Adam perspective fix.jpg
Author: <bdi><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Michelangelo" class="extiw" title="w:en:Michelangelo"><span title="Italian artist and architect (1475–1564)">Michelangelo</span></a></bdi>
License: public domain
Credit: Michelangelo. This edit attempts to adjust the perspective caused by the camera lens and the ceiling gradient. The original photo is not perfectly parallel to the depth of the ceiling, which is why the bottom left could not be cropped. This edit tries to simulate what the painting would show if laid on a flat surface. Adam's head is notably more accurate after these changes. Without a laser mapping of the surface, a truly accurate reproduction is impossible.

<hr>
<span typeof="mw:File"><span><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/Dialog-warning.svg/40px-Dialog-warning.svg.png" decoding="async" width="25" height="25" class="mw-file-element" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/Dialog-warning.svg/50px-Dialog-warning.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="48" data-file-height="48"></span></span> <small>You must also include a <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Copyright_tags/Country-specific_tags#United_States_of_America" title="Commons:Copyright tags/Country-specific tags">United States public domain tag</a> to indicate why this work is in the public domain in the United States.<div class="navigation-not-searchable"> Note that a few countries have copyright terms longer than 70 years: Mexico has 100 years, Jamaica has 95 years, Colombia has 80 years, and Guatemala and Samoa have 75 years. This image may <i>not</i> be in the public domain in these countries, which moreover do <i>not</i> implement the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/rule_of_the_shorter_term" class="extiw" title="w:rule of the shorter term">rule of the shorter term</a>. Honduras has a general copyright term of 75 years, but it <i>does</i> implement the rule of the shorter term. Copyright may extend on works created by French who died for France in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_War_II" class="extiw" title="w:World War II">World War II</a> (<a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Copyright_rules_by_territory/France" title="Commons:Copyright rules by territory/France">more information</a>), Russians who served in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eastern_Front_(World_War_II)" class="extiw" title="w:Eastern Front (World War II)">the Eastern Front of World War II</a> (known as the Great Patriotic War in Russia) and posthumously <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rehabilitation_(Soviet)" class="extiw" title="w:Rehabilitation (Soviet)">rehabilitated</a> victims of Soviet repressions (<a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:PD-Russia" title="Template:PD-Russia">more information</a>).</div></small>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2" style="text-align:center;font-size:x-small;line-height:140%;"><a href="https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/deed.en" class="extiw" title="ccorg:publicdomain/mark/1.0/deed.en">This file has been identified as being free of known restrictions under copyright law, including all related and neighboring rights.</a>
</td></tr></tbody></table><span class="licensetpl_link" style="display:none;">https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/</span><span class="licensetpl_short" style="display:none;">PDM</span><span class="licensetpl_long" style="display:none;">Creative Commons Public Domain Mark 1.0</span><span class="licensetpl_link_req" style="display:none;">false</span><span class="licensetpl_attr_req" style="display:none;">false</span>
</div>

<td><small><b>Warnings:</b></small><br><div style="font-size:85%;">
<ul><li>Use of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NASA_logo" class="extiw" title="w:NASA logo">NASA logos</a>, insignia and emblems is restricted per U.S. law <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.govinfo.gov/app/details/CFR-2021-title14-vol5/CFR-2021-title14-vol5-part1221/summary">14 CFR 1221</a>.</li>
<li>The NASA website hosts a large number of images from the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soviet_space_program" class="extiw" title="w:Soviet space program">Soviet</a>/<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russian_Federal_Space_Agency" class="extiw" title="w:Russian Federal Space Agency">Russian space agency</a>, and other non-American space agencies. These are <i>not necessarily</i> in the public domain.</li>
<li>Materials based on <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hubble_Space_Telescope" class="extiw" title="w:Hubble Space Telescope">Hubble Space Telescope</a> data may be copyrighted if they are not explicitly produced by the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Space_Telescope_Science_Institute" class="extiw" title="w:Space Telescope Science Institute">STScI</a>.<a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://hubblesite.org/copyright/">[1]</a> See also <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:PD-Hubble" title="Template:PD-Hubble"><span style="font-family:monospace,monospace;">{{PD-Hubble}}</span></a> and <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:Cc-Hubble" class="mw-redirect" title="Template:Cc-Hubble"><span style="font-family:monospace,monospace;">{{Cc-Hubble}}</span></a>.</li>
<li>The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solar_and_Heliospheric_Observatory" class="extiw" title="w:Solar and Heliospheric Observatory">SOHO (ESA &amp; NASA)</a> joint project implies that all materials created by its probe are copyrighted and require permission for commercial non-educational use. <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://sohowww.nascom.nasa.gov/data/summary/copyright.html">[2]</a></li>
<li>Images featured on the <i><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astronomy_Picture_of_the_Day" class="extiw" title="w:Astronomy Picture of the Day">Astronomy Picture of the Day</a></i> (APOD) web site may be copyrighted. <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://apod.nasa.gov/apod/lib/about_apod.html#srapply">[3]</a></li>
<li>The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Space_Science_Data_Center" class="extiw" title="w:National Space Science Data Center">National Space Science Data Center</a> (NSSDC) site has been known to host <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Village_pump/Copyright/Archive/2014/08#Copyright_status_of_File:Venera_13_-_ven13right.png" title="Commons:Village pump/Copyright/Archive/2014/08">copyrighted content</a>. Title: File:Osaka (Chinese characters).svg
Author: <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/w/index.php?title=White_whirlwind&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="White whirlwind (page does not exist)">White whirlwind</a>
License: public domain
Credit: <span class="int-own-work" lang="en">Own work</span>
Permission: <i>The depicted text is <b>ineligible for <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Copyrights" class="extiw" title="w:Copyrights">copyright</a></b> and therefore in the <b><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/public_domain" class="extiw" title="w:public domain">public domain</a></b> because it is not a “literary work” or other protected type in sense of the local copyright law. Facts, data, and unoriginal information which is common property without sufficiently creative authorship in a general typeface or basic handwriting, and simple geometric shapes are not protected by copyright.</i>
<small>This tag does not generally apply to all images of texts. Particular countries can have different legal definition of the “literary work” as the subject of copyright and different courts' interpretation practices. Some countries protect almost every written work, while other countries protect distinctively artistic or scientific texts and databases only. Extent of creativeness, function and length of the text can be relevant. The copyright protection can be limited to the literary form – the included information itself can be excluded from protection.</small>

<td><i>According to <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20181002142928/http://elaws.e-gov.go.jp/search/elawsSearch/elaws_search/lsg0500/detail?lawId=345AC0000000048&amp;openerCode=1">Japanese Copyright Law (June 1, 2018 grant)</a>, the work is now in the <b><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/public_domain" class="extiw" title="w:public domain">public domain</a></b> in Japan because the copyrights of the <b>works in names of organizations, in Japan</b> expire in 50 years after the publication, or in 50 years after the creation if the works are not published within 50 years after the creation (article 53).</i>
<div class="center"><i>To uploader: <b>Please provide a name of organization and year of publication and source.</b></i></div>
<p><b>Note:</b> <b>The enforcement of the revised Copyright Act on December 30, 2018 extended the copyright term of works whose copyright was valid on that day to 70 years. Do not use this template for works published after 1967.</b>
</p><p><small>Please note that being in the public domain in Japan does <b>not</b> automatically mean that it is free as well in the United States.  Find and add one of the <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:PD_US_license_tags" title="Category:PD US license tags">PD US license tags</a> in order to ensure that the file is free in the United States. Typically, for a published work to be in the public domain in the United States, it needs to be published before <b>1946</b>, because of <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:URAA-restored_copyrights" title="Commons:URAA-restored copyrights">URAA-restored copyrights</a>.  Unpublished works need to satisfy <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:PD-US-unpublished" title="Template:PD-US-unpublished"><span style="font-family:monospace,monospace;">{{PD-US-unpublished}}</span></a>.</small>

<li>(ii) notifications, instructions, circular notices and the like issued by organs of the State or local public entities, independent administrative organs ("independent administrative organs" means those mentioned in Article 2, paragraph (1) of the Law for General Rules for Independent Administrative Organs (Law No.103, of 1999); the same shall apply hereinafter) or local independent administrative organs ("local independent administrative organs" means those mentioned in Article 2, paragraph (1) of the Law for Local Independent Administrative Organs (Law No.118, of 2003); the same shall apply hereinafter);</li>
<li>(iii) judgments, decisions, orders and decrees of law courts, as well as rulings and decisions made by administrative organs in proceedings similar to judicial ones;</li>
<li>(iv) translations and compilations, of those materials mentioned in the preceding three items, made by organs of the State or local public entities, independent administrative organs or local independent administrative organs.</li></ul>

<td><i>According to <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20181002142928/http://elaws.e-gov.go.jp/search/elawsSearch/elaws_search/lsg0500/detail?lawId=345AC0000000048&amp;openerCode=1">Japanese Copyright Law (June 1, 2018 grant)</a>, the work is now in the <b><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/public_domain" class="extiw" title="w:public domain">public domain</a></b> in Japan because the copyrights of the <b>works in names of organizations, in Japan</b> expire in 50 years after the publication, or in 50 years after the creation if the works are not published within 50 years after the creation (article 53).</i>
<div class="center"><i>To uploader: <b>Please provide a name of organization and year of publication and source.</b></i></div>
<p><b>Note:</b> <b>The enforcement of the revised Copyright Act on December 30, 2018 extended the copyright term of works whose copyright was valid on that day to 70 years. Do not use this template for works published after 1967.</b>
</p><p><small>Please note that being in the public domain in Japan does <b>not</b> automatically mean that it is free as well in the United States.  Find and add one of the <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:PD_US_license_tags" title="Category:PD US license tags">PD US license tags</a> in order to ensure that the file is free in the United States. Typically, for a published work to be in the public domain in the United States, it needs to be published before <b>1946</b>, because of <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:URAA-restored_copyrights" title="Commons:URAA-restored copyrights">URAA-restored copyrights</a>.  Unpublished works need to satisfy <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:PD-US-unpublished" title="Template:PD-US-unpublished"><span style="font-family:monospace,monospace;">{{PD-US-unpublished}}</span></a>.</small>

<td><i>This work may <b>not</b> be in the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/public_domain" class="extiw" title="w:public domain">public domain</a> <b>in the United States</b> because its U.S. copyright was restored by the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/URAA" class="extiw" title="en:URAA">URAA</a> as it was still copyrighted in its source country (<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Japan" class="extiw" title="w:en:Japan"><span title="island country in East Asia">Japan</span></a>) on the URAA date (1 January 1996). In most cases, it is <b>copyrighted in the U.S.</b> until <b>95 years</b> after the year in which it was initially published (exceptions are works published after 1977; see <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Hirtle_chart" title="Commons:Hirtle chart">Commons:Hirtle chart</a>).</i> <b>This template may not be used for files uploaded after 1 March 2012.</b>
<p>If you are the copyright holder of this file, and do not wish to have it hosted on Commons, please contact our <a href="https://foundation.wikimedia.org/wiki/Designated_agent" class="extiw" title="wmf:Designated agent">designated agent</a> or <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Deletion_requests" title="Commons:Deletion requests">nominate the file for deletion</a>, explaining the situation.

Title: File:A Titan lake.jpg
Author: NASA/JPL

<td><small><b>Warnings:</b></small><br><div style="font-size:85%;">
<ul><li>Use of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NASA_logo" class="extiw" title="w:NASA logo">NASA logos</a>, insignia and emblems is restricted per U.S. law <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.govinfo.gov/app/details/CFR-2021-title14-vol5/CFR-2021-title14-vol5-part1221/summary">14 CFR 1221</a>.</li>
<li>The NASA website hosts a large number of images from the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soviet_space_program" class="extiw" title="w:Soviet space program">Soviet</a>/<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russian_Federal_Space_Agency" class="extiw" title="w:Russian Federal Space Agency">Russian space agency</a>, and other non-American space agencies. These are <i>not necessarily</i> in the public domain.</li>
<li>Materials based on <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hubble_Space_Telescope" class="extiw" title="w:Hubble Space Telescope">Hubble Space Telescope</a> data may be copyrighted if they are not explicitly produced by the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Space_Telescope_Science_Institute" class="extiw" title="w:Space Telescope Science Institute">STScI</a>.<a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://hubblesite.org/copyright/">[1]</a> See also <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:PD-Hubble" title="Template:PD-Hubble"><span style="font-family:monospace,monospace;">{{PD-Hubble}}</span></a> and <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:Cc-Hubble" class="mw-redirect" title="Template:Cc-Hubble"><span style="font-family:monospace,monospace;">{{Cc-Hubble}}</span></a>.</li>
<li>The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solar_and_Heliospheric_Observatory" class="extiw" title="w:Solar and Heliospheric Observatory">SOHO (ESA &amp; NASA)</a> joint project implies that all materials created by its probe are copyrighted and require permission for commercial non-educational use. <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://sohowww.nascom.nasa.gov/data/summary/copyright.html">[2]</a></li>
<li>Images featured on the <i><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astronomy_Picture_of_the_Day" class="extiw" title="w:Astronomy Picture of the Day">Astronomy Picture of the Day</a></i> (APOD) web site may be copyrighted. <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://apod.nasa.gov/apod/lib/about_apod.html#srapply">[3]</a></li>
<li>The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Space_Science_Data_Center" class="extiw" title="w:National Space Science Data Center">National Space Science Data Center</a> (NSSDC) site has been known to host <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Village_pump/Copyright/Archive/2014/08#Copyright_status_of_File:Venera_13_-_ven13right.png" title="Commons:Village pump/Copyright/Archive/2014/08">copyrighted content</a>. Its <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/photo_gallery/photogallery-faq.html#use">photo gallery FAQ</a> states that all of the images in the photo gallery are in the public domain "Unless otherwise noted."</li></ul></div>
</td></tr></tbody></table>

<td><small><b>Warnings:</b></small><br><div style="font-size:85%;">
<ul><li>Use of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NASA_logo" class="extiw" title="w:NASA logo">NASA logos</a>, insignia and emblems is restricted per U.S. law <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.govinfo.gov/app/details/CFR-2021-title14-vol5/CFR-2021-title14-vol5-part1221/summary">14 CFR 1221</a>.</li>
<li>The NASA website hosts a large number of images from the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soviet_space_program" class="extiw" title="w:Soviet space program">Soviet</a>/<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russian_Federal_Space_Agency" class="extiw" title="w:Russian Federal Space Agency">Russian space agency</a>, and other non-American space agencies. These are <i>not necessarily</i> in the public domain.</li>
<li>Materials based on <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hubble_Space_Telescope" class="extiw" title="w:Hubble Space Telescope">Hubble Space Telescope</a> data may be copyrighted if they are not explicitly produced by the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Space_Telescope_Science_Institute" class="extiw" title="w:Space Telescope Science Institute">STScI</a>.<a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://hubblesite.org/copyright/">[1]</a> See also <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:PD-Hubble" title="Template:PD-Hubble"><span style="font-family:monospace,monospace;">{{PD-Hubble}}</span></a> and <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:Cc-Hubble" class="mw-redirect" title="Template:Cc-Hubble"><span style="font-family:monospace,monospace;">{{Cc-Hubble}}</span></a>.</li>
<li>The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solar_and_Heliospheric_Observatory" class="extiw" title="w:Solar and Heliospheric Observatory">SOHO (ESA &amp; NASA)</a> joint project implies that all materials created by its probe are copyrighted and require permission for commercial non-educational use. <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://sohowww.nascom.nasa.gov/data/summary/copyright.html">[2]</a></li>
<li>Images featured on the <i><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astronomy_Picture_of_the_Day" class="extiw" title="w:Astronomy Picture of the Day">Astronomy Picture of the Day</a></i> (APOD) web site may be copyrighted. <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://apod.nasa.gov/apod/lib/about_apod.html#srapply">[3]</a></li>
<li>The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Space_Science_Data_Center" class="extiw" title="w:National Space Science Data Center">National Space Science Data Center</a> (NSSDC) site has been known to host <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Village_pump/Copyright/Archive/2014/08#Copyright_status_of_File:Venera_13_-_ven13right.png" title="Commons:Village pump/Copyright/Archive/2014/08">copyrighted content</a>. Its <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/photo_gallery/photogallery-faq.html#use">photo gallery FAQ</a> states that all of the images in the photo gallery are in the public domain "Unless otherwise noted."</li></ul></div>

This image may <i>not</i> be in the public domain in these countries, which moreover do <i>not</i> implement the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/rule_of_the_shorter_term" class="extiw" title="w:rule of the shorter term">rule of the shorter term</a>. Honduras has a general copyright term of 75 years, but it <i>does</i> implement the rule of the shorter term. Copyright may extend on works created by French who died for France in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_War_II" class="extiw" title="w:World War II">World War II</a> (<a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Copyright_rules_by_territory/France" title="Commons:Copyright rules by territory/France">more information</a>), Russians who served in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eastern_Front_(World_War_II)" class="extiw" title="w:Eastern Front (World War II)">the Eastern Front of World War II</a> (known as the Great Patriotic War in Russia) and posthumously <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rehabilitation_(Soviet)" class="extiw" title="w:Rehabilitation (Soviet)">rehabilitated</a> victims of Soviet repressions (<a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:PD-Russia" title="Template:PD-Russia">more information</a>).</div></small>

Title: File:Marken-wapen.svg
Author: Unknown, SVG = <span class="int-own-work" lang="en">Own work</span>
License: public domain
Credit: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.therightproductions.nl/hogeraadvanadel/index.php?id=109&amp;wapen=611">Hoge Raad van Adel</a>
Permission: This image depicts a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coat_of_arms" class="extiw" title="en:Coat of arms">coat of arms</a> of a (former) Dutch governmental jurisdiction, municipality, province, water board (Dutch: "Waterschap") or diocese. These coats of arms have been registered with the <i><b>Hoge Raad van Adel</b></i> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.hogeraadvanadel.nl/instellingen">[1]</a>, and are/were being used by the organisation to which the coat of arms was granted by Royal Decree (Dutch: Koninklijk Besluit). Every person is allowed to use the image of the arms, with some restrictions, see fragment below of the Ministerial Notice <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.hogeraadvanadel.nl/binaries/hogeraadvanadel/documenten/circulaires/1979/09/03/circulaire-1979-09-03-gebruik-door-derden-van-wapens-van-publiekrechtelijke-lichamen/circulaire-1979-09-03-gebruik-door-derden-van-wapens-van-publiekrechtelijke-lichamen.pdf">of 3 September 1979 (Ministerie van Binnenlandse Zaken)</a> (Dutch).
<p><small>Fragment from the memo: <i>The depiction of a municipal coat of arms is allowed: the municipality holds no rights of creation of the coat of arms. There is also no objection against the use of a municipal coat of arms al for localising objects that are traded or that are being advertised, just as long it is ensured that no impression of municipal involvement or responsibility is created.</i></small>
</p>
In view of Dutch legislation the <b>use</b> of the arms or reproductions thereof is regarded as being in the <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Public_domain" class="mw-redirect" title="Public domain">public domain</a>. Everybody is allowed to make a drawing of the arms (on paper or electronically) in his/her own style based on the Royal Decree and claim it to be the arms of the municipality and uses it within the restrictions shown above. But there is copyright on each individual representation of the arms. This copyright lies with the artist that made that specific drawing based on the Royal Decree, not by the municipality.

This image may <i>not</i> be in the public domain in these countries, which moreover do <i>not</i> implement the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/rule_of_the_shorter_term" class="extiw" title="w:rule of the shorter term">rule of the shorter term</a>. Honduras has a general copyright term of 75 years, but it <i>does</i> implement the rule of the shorter term. Copyright may extend on works created by French who died for France in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_War_II" class="extiw" title="w:World War II">World War II</a> (<a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Copyright_rules_by_territory/France" title="Commons:Copyright rules by territory/France">more information</a>), Russians who served in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eastern_Front_(World_War_II)" class="extiw" title="w:Eastern Front (World War II)">the Eastern Front of World War II</a> (known as the Great Patriotic War in Russia) and posthumously <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rehabilitation_(Soviet)" class="extiw" title="w:Rehabilitation (Soviet)">rehabilitated</a> victims of Soviet repressions (<a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:PD-Russia" title="Template:PD-Russia">more information</a>).</div></small>

Title: File:Illas Cíes Topographic Map en (with shadows).png
Author: <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/w/index.php?title=User:Susana_Freixeiro&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="User:Susana Freixeiro (page does not exist)">Susana Freixeiro</a>

Credit: <p><span class="int-own-work" lang="en">Own work</span>

<ul><li>Topographic data from the <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www2.jpl.nasa.gov/srtm">NASA Shuttle Radar Topography Mission</a> (SRTM3 v.2) (public domain) edited with <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.visualizationsoftware.com/3dem.html">3DEM</a>, vectorized with <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inkscape" class="extiw" title="en:Inkscape">Inkscape</a>; Following <a href="https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikip%C3%A9dia:Atelier_graphique/Didacticiels_cartographiques/Didacticiel_de_cr%C3%A9ation_de_carte_topographique_vectorielle" class="extiw" title="fr:Wikipédia:Atelier graphique/Didacticiels cartographiques/Didacticiel de création de carte topographique vectorielle">this tutorial</a>.</li>
<li>Coast, cities, roads, boundaries : <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.openstreetmap.fr/">Openstreetmap</a> details corrected by aereal photography;</li>
<li>Locator map from <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Spain_Galicia_location_map.svg" title="File:Spain Galicia location map.svg">File:Spain Galicia location map.svg</a> by <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/User:Miguillen" title="User:Miguillen">User:Miguillen</a> ;</li>
<li>Others symbols from <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Maps_template-fr.svg" title="File:Maps template-fr.svg">File:Maps template-fr.svg</a></li>
<li>Toponymic and microtoponymic data taken from the <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://toponimia.xunta.es/gl/descargas/">Toponymy of Galicia Project</a>; placenames revised by the <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://cpapx.xunta.es/toponimia-oficial#Comisi%C3%B3n%20de%20/">Toponymy Comission of the Autonomous Government of Galicia</a>.</li></ul>

<p><b>Note:</b> <b>The enforcement of the revised Copyright Act on December 30, 2018 extended the copyright term of works whose copyright was valid on that day to 70 years. Do not use this template for works published after 1967.</b>
</p><p><small>Please note that being in the public domain in Japan does <b>not</b> automatically mean that it is free as well in the United States.  Find and add one of the <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:PD_US_license_tags" title="Category:PD US license tags">PD US license tags</a> in order to ensure that the file is free in the United States. Typically, for a published work to be in the public domain in the United States, it needs to be published before <b>1946</b>, because of <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:URAA-restored_copyrights" title="Commons:URAA-restored copyrights">URAA-restored copyrights</a>.  Unpublished works need to satisfy <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:PD-US-unpublished" title="Template:PD-US-unpublished"><span style="font-family:monospace,monospace;">{{PD-US-unpublished}}</span></a>.</small>

Permission: According to article 1276 of the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Civil_Code_of_Russia" class="extiw" title="en:Civil Code of Russia">Civil Code of Russia</a> in the amendment of October 1, 2014, it shall be allowed to reproduce "<i>works of architecture, of urban development, and of garden and landscape design</i>" for any purpose and without consent of the copyright holder(s), provided that these works are "<i>situated in places open for free attendance, or visible from such places</i>". Note that for any other kind of artwork, even if permanently situated in public place (for example, statues and monuments), this exception is still limited to non-commercial usage which is not compatible with <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Licensing" title="Commons:Licensing">Commons:Licensing</a>. For details, see <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:CRT/Russia#Freedom_of_panorama" class="mw-redirect" title="Commons:CRT/Russia">COM:CRT/Russia#Freedom of panorama</a>.

<td><div>Copyleft: This work of art is free; you can redistribute it and/or modify it according to terms of the <b><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Free_Art_License" class="extiw" title="w:en:Free Art License">Free Art License</a></b>. <td>
<figure class="mw-halign-right" typeof="mw:File"><a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Emblem-section.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/76/Emblem-section.svg/150px-Emblem-section.svg.png" decoding="async" width="150" height="150" class="mw-file-element" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/76/Emblem-section.svg/225px-Emblem-section.svg.png 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/76/Emblem-section.svg/300px-Emblem-section.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="48" data-file-height="48"></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>
<p>Bilder des zentralen Medienarchivs <a href="https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikimedia_Commons" class="extiw" title="de:Wikimedia Commons">Wikimedia Commons</a>, unterstehen einer <a href="https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Freie_Lizenz" class="extiw" title="de:Freie Lizenz">Freien Lizenz</a>. Diese Freiheit bedeutet nicht, dass dadurch das <a href="https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Urheberrecht" class="extiw" title="de:Urheberrecht">Urheberrecht</a> entfällt. Ganz im Gegenteil: <b>Als Gegenleistung für die kostenlose (nichtgewerbliche) Nutzung muss der Weiternutzer nur die <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Weiterverwendung" class="mw-redirect" title="Commons:Weiterverwendung">Lizenzbedingungen</a> einhalten und den Fotografen (meinen vollständigen Klarnamen <i>Wladyslaw Sojka</i> sowie die verlinkte Website www.sojka.photo) als <a href="https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Urheber" class="extiw" title="de:Urheber">Urheber</a> nennen.</b>   
</p><p>Juristisch ist die unterlassene Namensnennung eine <a href="https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Urheberrechtsverletzung" class="extiw" title="de:Urheberrechtsverletzung">Urheberrechtsverletzung</a> bzw. eine Verletzung der <a href="https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deutsches_Urheberrecht#Urheberpers%C3%B6nlichkeitsrecht" class="extiw" title="de:Deutsches Urheberrecht">Urheberpersönlichkeitsrechte</a>. Als Urheber kann ich mich gegen <i>Bilderklau</i> wehren, in dem ich einen Strafantrag stelle oder unmittelbar einen Rechtsanwalt beauftrage. Die Folge ist eine <a href="https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abmahnung" class="extiw" title="de:Abmahnung">Abmahnung</a> und die Aufforderung, eine strafbewehrte Unterlassungserklärung abzugeben.  
</p><p>So weit sollte es nicht kommen. Bitte achten Sie auf diese Regeln oder kontaktieren Sie mich im Zweifelsfall. Sollten Abweichungen von den hier angegebenen Regeln erwünscht sein, dann bedarf es auf jeden Fall einer ausdrücklichen Genehmigung von mir als Urheber des jeweiligen Bildes. 
</p><p>Kontaktmöglichkeiten: über Wikimedia Commons oder über <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.sojka.photo/">www.sojka.photo</a>.
</p>
</td></tr></tbody></table>

Title: File:Japan Factory Ship Nisshin Maru Whaling Mother and Calf.jpg
Author: Customs and Border Protection Service,  Commonwealth of Australia
License: cc by-sa 3.0 au
Credit: <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://www.customs.gov.au/webdata/resources/photogallery/AustralianCustoms-WhalingInTheSouthernOcean_5.jpg">http://www.customs.gov.au/webdata/resources/photogallery/AustralianCustoms-WhalingInTheSouthernOcean_5.jpg</a>
Permission: <p>NOTE: This file was originally uploaded to <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/" class="extiw" title="en:">en.Wikipedia</a> and assigned a "fair use" license.  I, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/User:Grolltech" class="extiw" title="en:User:Grolltech">Grolltech</a>, corrected the license to CC-BY-SA-3.0 for the following reasons:
</p>
<ul><li>In late 2008, Australia changed copyright licensing as follows:</li></ul>
 <blockquote>
<p><i><i>"The Commonwealth Copyright Administration (CCA) within the Attorney-General’s Department has been disbanded and no longer provides copyright licences allowing members of the public to re-use Commonwealth Government copyright material.  In line with a recommendation of the <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.finance.gov.au/publications/gov20taskforcereport/index.html">Government 2.0 Taskforce Report</a>, Commonwealth Government agencies are now required to release copyright public sector information under Creative Commons BY-licences or other open content licences, wherever possible."</i></i>
</p>
<p><cite style="font-style:normal;">—Home page, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ag.gov.au/Copyright/CommonwealthCopyrightAdministration/Pages/default.aspx">Australia's Commonwealth Copyright Administration</a></cite></p>
</blockquote>
<ul><li>Additionally, the Agency has already given <i>explicit</i> permission to use this file:</li></ul>
 <blockquote>
<p><i><i>"These images are provided for external use but please credit Australian Customs and Border Protection Service. Regards."</i></i>
</p>
<p><cite style="font-style:normal;">—David O'Sullivan, Online Communication Manager, Communication and Media, Australian Customs and Border Protection Service</cite></p>
</blockquote>

This image may <i>not</i> be in the public domain in these countries, which moreover do <i>not</i> implement the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/rule_of_the_shorter_term" class="extiw" title="w:rule of the shorter term">rule of the shorter term</a>. Honduras has a general copyright term of 75 years, but it <i>does</i> implement the rule of the shorter term. Copyright may extend on works created by French who died for France in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_War_II" class="extiw" title="w:World War II">World War II</a> (<a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Copyright_rules_by_territory/France" title="Commons:Copyright rules by territory/France">more information</a>), Russians who served in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eastern_Front_(World_War_II)" class="extiw" title="w:Eastern Front (World War II)">the Eastern Front of World War II</a> (known as the Great Patriotic War in Russia) and posthumously <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rehabilitation_(Soviet)" class="extiw" title="w:Rehabilitation (Soviet)">rehabilitated</a> victims of Soviet repressions (<a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:PD-Russia" title="Template:PD-Russia">more information</a>).</div></small>

Title: File:Reden und Vortrag zur Eroeffnung.png
Author: <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/w/index.php?title=User:Gta_verlag&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="User:Gta verlag (page does not exist)">Gta verlag</a>
License: public domain
Credit: <span class="int-own-work" lang="en">Own work</span>
Permission: <i>The depicted text is <b>ineligible for <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Copyrights" class="extiw" title="w:Copyrights">copyright</a></b> and therefore in the <b><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/public_domain" class="extiw" title="w:public domain">public domain</a></b> because it is not a “literary work” or other protected type in sense of the local copyright law. Facts, data, and unoriginal information which is common property without sufficiently creative authorship in a general typeface or basic handwriting, and simple geometric shapes are not protected by copyright.</i>
<small>This tag does not generally apply to all images of texts. Particular countries can have different legal definition of the “literary work” as the subject of copyright and different courts' interpretation practices. Some countries protect almost every written work, while other countries protect distinctively artistic or scientific texts and databases only. Extent of creativeness, function and length of the text can be relevant. The copyright protection can be limited to the literary form – the included information itself can be excluded from protection.</small>

<td><small><b>Warnings:</b></small><br><div style="font-size:85%;">
<ul><li>Use of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NASA_logo" class="extiw" title="w:NASA logo">NASA logos</a>, insignia and emblems is restricted per U.S. law <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.govinfo.gov/app/details/CFR-2021-title14-vol5/CFR-2021-title14-vol5-part1221/summary">14 CFR 1221</a>.</li>
<li>The NASA website hosts a large number of images from the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soviet_space_program" class="extiw" title="w:Soviet space program">Soviet</a>/<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russian_Federal_Space_Agency" class="extiw" title="w:Russian Federal Space Agency">Russian space agency</a>, and other non-American space agencies. These are <i>not necessarily</i> in the public domain.</li>
<li>Materials based on <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hubble_Space_Telescope" class="extiw" title="w:Hubble Space Telescope">Hubble Space Telescope</a> data may be copyrighted if they are not explicitly produced by the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Space_Telescope_Science_Institute" class="extiw" title="w:Space Telescope Science Institute">STScI</a>.<a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://hubblesite.org/copyright/">[1]</a> See also <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:PD-Hubble" title="Template:PD-Hubble"><span style="font-family:monospace,monospace;">{{PD-Hubble}}</span></a> and <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:Cc-Hubble" class="mw-redirect" title="Template:Cc-Hubble"><span style="font-family:monospace,monospace;">{{Cc-Hubble}}</span></a>.</li>
<li>The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solar_and_Heliospheric_Observatory" class="extiw" title="w:Solar and Heliospheric Observatory">SOHO (ESA &amp; NASA)</a> joint project implies that all materials created by its probe are copyrighted and require permission for commercial non-educational use. <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://sohowww.nascom.nasa.gov/data/summary/copyright.html">[2]</a></li>
<li>Images featured on the <i><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astronomy_Picture_of_the_Day" class="extiw" title="w:Astronomy Picture of the Day">Astronomy Picture of the Day</a></i> (APOD) web site may be copyrighted. <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://apod.nasa.gov/apod/lib/about_apod.html#srapply">[3]</a></li>
<li>The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Space_Science_Data_Center" class="extiw" title="w:National Space Science Data Center">National Space Science Data Center</a> (NSSDC) site has been known to host <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Village_pump/Copyright/Archive/2014/08#Copyright_status_of_File:Venera_13_-_ven13right.png" title="Commons:Village pump/Copyright/Archive/2014/08">copyrighted content</a>. Its <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/photo_gallery/photogallery-faq.html#use">photo gallery FAQ</a> states that all of the images in the photo gallery are in the public domain "Unless otherwise noted."</li></ul></div>

<td><small><b>Warnings:</b></small><br><div style="font-size:85%;">
<ul><li>Use of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NASA_logo" class="extiw" title="w:NASA logo">NASA logos</a>, insignia and emblems is restricted per U.S. law <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.govinfo.gov/app/details/CFR-2021-title14-vol5/CFR-2021-title14-vol5-part1221/summary">14 CFR 1221</a>.</li>
<li>The NASA website hosts a large number of images from the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soviet_space_program" class="extiw" title="w:Soviet space program">Soviet</a>/<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russian_Federal_Space_Agency" class="extiw" title="w:Russian Federal Space Agency">Russian space agency</a>, and other non-American space agencies. These are <i>not necessarily</i> in the public domain.</li>
<li>Materials based on <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hubble_Space_Telescope" class="extiw" title="w:Hubble Space Telescope">Hubble Space Telescope</a> data may be copyrighted if they are not explicitly produced by the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Space_Telescope_Science_Institute" class="extiw" title="w:Space Telescope Science Institute">STScI</a>.<a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://hubblesite.org/copyright/">[1]</a> See also <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:PD-Hubble" title="Template:PD-Hubble"><span style="font-family:monospace,monospace;">{{PD-Hubble}}</span></a> and <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:Cc-Hubble" class="mw-redirect" title="Template:Cc-Hubble"><span style="font-family:monospace,monospace;">{{Cc-Hubble}}</span></a>.</li>
<li>The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solar_and_Heliospheric_Observatory" class="extiw" title="w:Solar and Heliospheric Observatory">SOHO (ESA &amp; NASA)</a> joint project implies that all materials created by its probe are copyrighted and require permission for commercial non-educational use. <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://sohowww.nascom.nasa.gov/data/summary/copyright.html">[2]</a></li>
<li>Images featured on the <i><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astronomy_Picture_of_the_Day" class="extiw" title="w:Astronomy Picture of the Day">Astronomy Picture of the Day</a></i> (APOD) web site may be copyrighted. <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://apod.nasa.gov/apod/lib/about_apod.html#srapply">[3]</a></li>
<li>The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Space_Science_Data_Center" class="extiw" title="w:National Space Science Data Center">National Space Science Data Center</a> (NSSDC) site has been known to host <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Village_pump/Copyright/Archive/2014/08#Copyright_status_of_File:Venera_13_-_ven13right.png" title="Commons:Village pump/Copyright/Archive/2014/08">copyrighted content</a>. Its <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/photo_gallery/photogallery-faq.html#use">photo gallery FAQ</a> states that all of the images in the photo gallery are in the public domain "Unless otherwise noted."</li></ul></div>

<td rowspan="2"><span typeof="mw:File"><span title="Public domain"><img alt="Public domain" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/62/PD-icon.svg/120px-PD-icon.svg.png" decoding="async" width="64" height="64" class="mw-file-element" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/62/PD-icon.svg/128px-PD-icon.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="196" data-file-height="196"></span></span>

<td>
<p>This work is in the <b><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/public_domain" class="extiw" title="en:public domain">public domain</a></b> in its country of origin and other countries and areas where the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_countries%27_copyright_lengths" class="extiw" title="w:List of countries' copyright lengths">copyright term</a> is the author's <b>life plus 70 years or fewer</b>.
</p>
<hr>
<span typeof="mw:File"><span><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/Dialog-warning.svg/40px-Dialog-warning.svg.png" decoding="async" width="25" height="25" class="mw-file-element" srcset="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/Dialog-warning.svg/50px-Dialog-warning.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="48" data-file-height="48"></span></span> <small>You must also include a <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Copyright_tags/Country-specific_tags#United_States_of_America" title="Commons:Copyright tags/Country-specific tags">United States public domain tag</a> to indicate why this work is in the public domain in the United States.<div class="navigation-not-searchable"> Note that a few countries have copyright terms longer than 70 years: Mexico has 100 years, Jamaica has 95 years, Colombia has 80 years, and Guatemala and Samoa have 75 years. This image may <i>not</i> be in the public domain in these countries, which moreover do <i>not</i> implement the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/rule_of_the_shorter_term" class="extiw" title="w:rule of the shorter term">rule of the shorter term</a>. Honduras has a general copyright term of 75 years, but it <i>does</i> implement the rule of the shorter term. Copyright may extend on works created by French who died for France in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_War_II" class="extiw" title="w:World War II">World War II</a> (<a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Copyright_rules_by_territory/France" title="Commons:Copyright rules by territory/France">more information</a>), Russians who served in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eastern_Front_(World_War_II)" class="extiw" title="w:Eastern Front (World War II)">the Eastern Front of World War II</a> (known as the Great Patriotic War in Russia) and posthumously <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rehabilitation_(Soviet)" class="extiw" title="w:Rehabilitation (Soviet)">rehabilitated</a> victims of Soviet repressions (<a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:PD-Russia" title="Template:PD-Russia">more information</a>).</div></small>
</td></tr>

<ul><li>Use of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NASA_logo" class="extiw" title="w:NASA logo">NASA logos</a>, insignia and emblems is restricted per U.S. law <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.govinfo.gov/app/details/CFR-2021-title14-vol5/CFR-2021-title14-vol5-part1221/summary">14 CFR 1221</a>.</li>
<li>The NASA website hosts a large number of images from the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soviet_space_program" class="extiw" title="w:Soviet space program">Soviet</a>/<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russian_Federal_Space_Agency" class="extiw" title="w:Russian Federal Space Agency">Russian space agency</a>, and other non-American space agencies. These are <i>not necessarily</i> in the public domain.</li>
<li>Materials based on <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hubble_Space_Telescope" class="extiw" title="w:Hubble Space Telescope">Hubble Space Telescope</a> data may be copyrighted if they are not explicitly produced by the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Space_Telescope_Science_Institute" class="extiw" title="w:Space Telescope Science Institute">STScI</a>.<a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://hubblesite.org/copyright/">[2]</a> See also <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:PD-Hubble" title="Template:PD-Hubble"><span style="font-family:monospace,monospace;">{{PD-Hubble}}</span></a> and <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Template:Cc-Hubble" class="mw-redirect" title="Template:Cc-Hubble"><span style="font-family:monospace,monospace;">{{Cc-Hubble}}</span></a>.</li>
<li>The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solar_and_Heliospheric_Observatory" class="extiw" title="w:Solar and Heliospheric Observatory">SOHO (ESA &amp; NASA)</a> joint project implies that all materials created by its probe are copyrighted and require permission for commercial non-educational use. <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://sohowww.nascom.nasa.gov/data/summary/copyright.html">[3]</a></li>
<li>Images featured on the <i><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astronomy_Picture_of_the_Day" class="extiw" title="w:Astronomy Picture of the Day">Astronomy Picture of the Day</a></i> (APOD) web site may be copyrighted. <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://apod.nasa.gov/apod/lib/about_apod.html#srapply">[4]</a></li>
<li>The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Space_Science_Data_Center" class="extiw" title="w:National Space Science Data Center">National Space Science Data Center</a> (NSSDC) site has been known to host <a href="//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Village_pump/Copyright/Archive/2014/08#Copyright_status_of_File:Venera_13_-_ven13right.png" title="Commons:Village pump/Copyright/Archive/2014/08">copyrighted content</a>.
